{
  "stem": "1502.5",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 197,
      "text": "He was a Belgian SS.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 198,
      "text": "His name was Van Kolh.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 199,
      "text": "And we called him the Horsehead, [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 200,
      "text": "Because he looked like a horse.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 201,
      "text": "His-- he had a head like a horse head.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 202,
      "text": "He was the most brutal of all the SS.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 203,
      "text": "Now, Mechelen-- the commander of the camp was a German.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 204,
      "text": "His name was Frank.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 205,
      "text": "He was a German officer.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 206,
      "text": "He was a middle-aged-- middle-aged man.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 207,
      "text": "He was not the main commander.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 208,
      "text": "Because the camp belonged-- as I mentioned before, there was another camp, Breendonk.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 209,
      "text": "And this was a branch, really, from Breendonk.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 210,
      "text": "The commander from Breendonk was a higher-ranking officer.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 211,
      "text": "He was a sturmbannfuhrer.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 212,
      "text": "This was a major in the SS.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 213,
      "text": "And our commander was a lower SS officer.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 214,
      "text": "He was obersturmfuhrer.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 215,
      "text": "Which is like a lieutenant or a little more than a lieutenant.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 216,
      "text": "He was assisted by another German.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 217,
      "text": "His name was Boden.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 218,
      "text": "He was the assistant commander of the-- of the camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 219,
      "text": "He was also German.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 220,
      "text": "They were both police officers before the war, we found out later, in Leipzig.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 221,
      "text": "They joined the Nazi party.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 222,
      "text": "And they became big shots in the SS.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 223,
      "text": "They were the commanders.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 224,
      "text": "Then, there was another German officer, which we called [?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 225,
      "text": "Moshe-- ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 226,
      "text": "Moshe ?] [GERMAN], Moshe the Precise, because he wanted everything to precision.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 227,
      "text": "For instance, there was a law that you had to salute a German officer a number of feet away from you.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 228,
      "text": "When you saw a German officer, 20 feet, you had to take off your hat and salute him in a certain manner, which they taught us.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 229,
      "text": "If you didn't, he could beat you up or put you in the corner with a wait for two hours, which he did to my father.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we called him-- he was German also.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
